A surreal vintage illustration of a person gazing into an ornate antique mirror, but their reflection shows a completely different, idealized version of themselves with a confident pose and golden aura, while the actual figure appears uncertain and smaller. The mirror frame is elaborate Victorian brass with intricate scrollwork. The background features warm sepia tones and aged paper texture with subtle cracks. Soft candlelight casts long shadows, creating a dreamlike atmosphere. The reflection seems to lean forward slightly, as if whispering reassurances. Moths flutter around the candle flame, symbolizing attraction to illusion. The color palette emphasizes amber, burnt sienna, and faded cream tones typical of 1920s illustration style.
